1
00:01:53,340 --> 00:01:53,970
Alright.

2
00:01:54,510 --> 00:01:57,850
We know they'll attack
from this shore at dawn,

3
00:01:58,810 --> 00:02:03,350
and that the only route into
the village from here is this slope.

4
00:02:03,350 --> 00:02:06,940
The cliffs are too steep
everywhere else.

5
00:02:06,940 --> 00:02:10,360
In other words, if we
defend this slope at all costs,

6
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:12,740
the village will be safe!

7
00:02:12,740 --> 00:02:14,780
Oh! That's easy!

8
00:02:14,780 --> 00:02:17,950
It's easy to say,
but we still have to fight!

9
00:02:17,950 --> 00:02:19,370
What can you guys do?

10
00:02:19,370 --> 00:02:20,240
Cut.

11
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,160
Stretch.

12
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:22,290
Steal.

13
00:02:22,460 --> 00:02:23,500
I can hide.

14
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:25,380
– You're gonna fight!
– You're gonna fight!

15
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:28,670
I was just kidding, c'mon!

16
00:02:30,460 --> 00:02:32,220
Oh, Klahadore!

17
00:02:32,220 --> 00:02:33,340
Welcome back!

18
00:02:33,340 --> 00:02:34,630
How is Miss Kaya?

19
00:02:34,630 --> 00:02:36,180
She's resting now.

20
00:02:36,180 --> 00:02:38,720
The whole affair really wore her out...

21
00:02:39,470 --> 00:02:43,890
To think such a thing happened
while I was in the neighboring town...

22
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:47,520
That Usopp boy certainly
is a troublemaker.

23
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,730
Indeed...

24
00:02:48,730 --> 00:02:52,610
And claiming you were
a pirate of all things…

25
00:02:53,070 --> 00:02:55,030
It's not even a good lie!

26
00:02:59,490 --> 00:03:01,740
Is that so...?

27
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,540
What is this?

28
00:03:05,540 --> 00:03:09,040
Oh, that is a present
from the miss to you.

29
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:13,590
She said it's your
third year at the mansion,

30
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:15,800
so it's a sort of commemoration.

31
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:17,430
A commemoration...

32
00:03:17,430 --> 00:03:20,930
Your current glasses
seem to slip often,

33
00:03:20,930 --> 00:03:23,430
so she custom-ordered those!

34
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:26,690
She's such a nice, thoughtful person!

35
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:31,480
A commemoration, you say...?

36
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:34,440
Indeed, tomorrow
is a day to commemorate.

37
00:03:35,110 --> 00:03:35,820
Huh?

38
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:43,370
It's a crescent moon tonight.

39
00:03:43,370 --> 00:03:44,700
Hm?

40
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:49,380
Nights like this make my heart race...

41
00:03:49,380 --> 00:03:52,630
and my blood stir...

42
00:03:55,010 --> 00:03:57,010
K-Klahadore!

43
00:03:57,010 --> 00:04:00,510
Wh-Why did you
break Miss Kaya's gift?!

44
00:04:01,260 --> 00:04:03,720
A gift? Oh, I'll be accepting
a gift, all right...

45
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:06,600
but not this paltry trinket.

46
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:08,690
It will be this entire mansion!

47
00:04:09,770 --> 00:04:12,020
Wh-What are you saying?!

48
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:14,940
I guess there's no need
to continue this charade.

49
00:04:15,610 --> 00:04:19,950
After all, there's going to be
an accident in a few hours...

50
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:27,540
It truly has been a long three years!

51
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:29,420
Miss Kaya! Run!

52
00:04:48,020 --> 00:04:50,020
Captain Jango!

53
00:04:51,350 --> 00:04:54,770
It's almost daybreak!
Please wake up, Captain Jango!

54
00:04:56,730 --> 00:04:58,360
Good morning, Captain!

55
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,200
Good morning!

56
00:05:00,820 --> 00:05:02,070
You morons!

57
00:05:02,070 --> 00:05:06,160
My policy is to say "good morning"
when the sun is up!

58
00:05:06,540 --> 00:05:08,040
Looks like he's in a bad mood.

59
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:09,660
He did just wake up...

60
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,580
Look!

61
00:05:11,580 --> 00:05:14,210
The moon's still up,
and it's the middle of the night.

62
00:05:14,210 --> 00:05:16,210
How dare you raise your voices!

63
00:05:16,210 --> 00:05:18,510
– Our apologies, sir! We're sorry, sir!
– Our apologies, sir! We're sorry, sir!

64
00:05:23,090 --> 00:05:24,720
Alright then, good morning.

65
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:27,930
Good morning? That's the
opposite of what he just said!

66
00:05:27,930 --> 00:05:31,890
You idiot! He's in a better
mood now, that's all!

67
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:32,980
Now, men!

68
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:35,520
Set sail!

69
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,230
– Aye, aye!
– Aye, aye!

70
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:43,950
Alright! Perfect!

71
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:48,120
They won't be able to climb
up this slope anymore...

72
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:51,410
thanks to all the oil
we've poured on it!

73
00:05:51,790 --> 00:05:57,380
We'll attack 'em while
they slip and slide around!

74
00:05:57,710 --> 00:05:59,710
Oil, huh...?

75
00:05:59,710 --> 00:06:02,930
No matter what,
we will protect this slope!

76
00:06:02,930 --> 00:06:06,180
Let's just hope that
none of us slip down there.

77
00:06:06,180 --> 00:06:08,930
It'd be pretty dumb to get
caught in our own trap.

78
00:06:08,930 --> 00:06:12,850
You sure did come up
with a slick plan!

79
00:06:12,850 --> 00:06:14,270
O-Of course!

80
00:06:14,270 --> 00:06:19,150
I have complete confidence
in my slingshot and daring ideas!

81
00:06:24,280 --> 00:06:25,700
It's almost dawn.

82
00:06:26,530 --> 00:06:27,490
Any moment now.

83
00:06:44,380 --> 00:06:46,220
We're here!

84
00:06:47,550 --> 00:06:48,930
Alright!

85
00:06:48,930 --> 00:06:52,520
Men, get ashore! Trash the village
and then head to the mansion!

86
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:53,890
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

87
00:06:53,890 --> 00:06:56,650
Captain! There are a couple
of strange boats here!

88
00:06:56,650 --> 00:06:58,060
What?!

89
00:06:58,650 --> 00:07:00,320
Should we check 'em out?

90
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:01,690
Leave 'em.

91
00:07:01,690 --> 00:07:03,190
I doubt they've got treasure.

92
00:07:06,410 --> 00:07:10,450
Where are they?
The sky's all bright now.

93
00:07:10,450 --> 00:07:12,120
Where could they be?

94
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:14,120
Maybe they overslept or something?

95
00:07:17,670 --> 00:07:19,960
Say...

96
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,550
Maybe it's just me,

97
00:07:21,550 --> 00:07:24,550
but I swear I hear shouting
coming from somewhere...

98
00:07:29,140 --> 00:07:31,640
Yeah, I definitely hear something!

99
00:07:32,260 --> 00:07:33,980
N-Now that you mention it...

100
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:35,640
Hey! What is it?!

101
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:37,810
There's a place
just like this to the north!

102
00:07:38,770 --> 00:07:40,560
Don't tell me…!

103
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:43,320
You mean this is the wrong shore?!

104
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:47,610
This is where they had their
secret meeting, so I just assumed...

105
00:07:48,280 --> 00:07:51,830
Hey, hurry! They're gonna reach
the village! Where is this place?!

106
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:55,910
If you run straight north from here,
you'll get there in three minutes!

107
00:07:55,910 --> 00:08:00,250
It looks basically the same, so we just
need to stop them at the slope there!

108
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:01,130
Hold on...

109
00:08:01,130 --> 00:08:03,250
Oh no!

110
00:08:03,250 --> 00:08:07,260
The north shore is
where our boats are!

111
00:08:07,260 --> 00:08:08,590
They'll take our treasure!

112
00:08:08,590 --> 00:08:10,680
I'll get there in twenty seconds!

113
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:11,800
Dammit!

114
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:15,140
My brilliant oil trap
was all for nothing!

115
00:08:15,140 --> 00:08:16,980
My treasure...

116
00:08:16,980 --> 00:08:17,980
Hey!

117
00:08:17,980 --> 00:08:19,350
What're you doing? Let's go!

118
00:08:19,350 --> 00:08:20,980
Yeah! We have to hurr–

119
00:08:24,030 --> 00:08:26,440
Help! I'm slipping!

120
00:08:27,030 --> 00:08:28,400
Let go, you moron!

121
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:28,990
Sorry!

122
00:08:30,030 --> 00:08:30,870
Perfect!

123
00:08:31,490 --> 00:08:32,910
Thanks, Zoro!

124
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:40,370
Sorry! The treasure's in danger!

125
00:08:40,370 --> 00:08:42,590
Try to get back up somehow!

126
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,250
That girl's gonna pay!

127
00:08:50,930 --> 00:08:53,100
I won't let them enter the village!

128
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:56,890
But man, Luffy sure runs fast...!

129
00:08:56,890 --> 00:08:58,520
I can't even see him anymore!

130
00:08:59,310 --> 00:09:02,520
Straight north!
Straight north! Straight north!

131
00:09:04,190 --> 00:09:07,490
They're dead meat if they
so much as touch my treasure!

132
00:09:15,950 --> 00:09:17,700
Someone's at the top of the slope!

133
00:09:20,370 --> 00:09:21,120
It's you!

134
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:35,850
My name is Captain Usopp!

135
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:38,180
I've been waiting for you all this time!

136
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:46,270
Wh-What the...?
I'm the first one here?!

137
00:09:46,270 --> 00:09:50,360
But he was running way ahead of me!

138
00:09:52,530 --> 00:09:54,160
Dammit!

139
00:09:54,740 --> 00:09:56,240
What do I do?!

140
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:58,490
I can't climb up!

141
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:04,040
I'm at the village now!

142
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,420
That's weird!

143
00:10:05,420 --> 00:10:08,420
He said north, so I ran
in the coldest direction!

144
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:19,430
You're that kid who overheard our plans.
What do you think you're doing?

145
00:10:19,430 --> 00:10:21,060
I-I'm warning you!

146
00:10:21,060 --> 00:10:22,690
Turn back while you still can!

147
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:27,860
Or else my crew of 100 million men
will beat the crap out of you guys!

148
00:10:29,860 --> 00:10:31,190
A hundred million?

149
00:10:31,190 --> 00:10:33,240
Hey now, no one's falling for that!

150
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:34,360
What?!

151
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:36,530
A hundred million?! W-Wow!

152
00:10:36,530 --> 00:10:38,410
He's obviously lying, Captain!

153
00:10:38,410 --> 00:10:39,950
He's so gullible...

154
00:10:40,330 --> 00:10:41,750
They saw through it?

155
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:44,620
He seriously thought
he could fool us, too...

156
00:10:44,620 --> 00:10:45,710
Why, you...!

157
00:10:45,710 --> 00:10:47,920
How dare you trick me!

158
00:10:47,920 --> 00:10:49,550
Captain Jango! I have news!

159
00:10:49,550 --> 00:10:50,840
Really?! Is it bad?!

160
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:52,010
No! It's not bad!

161
00:10:52,630 --> 00:10:54,840
We found treasure
on those strange boats!

162
00:10:55,220 --> 00:10:56,300
Lots of it, too!

163
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:58,640
Maybe four, no, five million berries!

164
00:10:58,640 --> 00:10:59,390
What?!

165
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:02,680
F-Five million berries...?!

166
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:05,940
Why do those guys have
that much money on their boats?

167
00:11:07,610 --> 00:11:09,770
So you found my treasure!

168
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:11,400
I'll let you have it!

169
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,490
What?! You'll give us the treasure?!

170
00:11:13,490 --> 00:11:14,360
That's right!

171
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:19,580
In exchange, all I ask is that
you leave immediately!

172
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:20,580
Wha...?!

173
00:11:20,580 --> 00:11:22,830
Is he really trying to buy us off?

174
00:11:22,830 --> 00:11:25,710
What a scummy guy!

175
00:11:26,330 --> 00:11:27,580
You fool...

176
00:11:27,580 --> 00:11:29,210
We're pirates.

177
00:11:29,210 --> 00:11:32,380
Of course we're going
to take the treasure!

178
00:11:33,090 --> 00:11:36,380
But that's no reason
for us to turn back.

179
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,850
Y-You have a point...

180
00:11:41,890 --> 00:11:46,390
Alright, then! On "one, two,
Jango," you'll let us pass!

181
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:49,400
It's that weapon from before!

182
00:11:49,900 --> 00:11:50,900
One...

183
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:51,690
two...

184
00:11:52,150 --> 00:11:52,690
Ja–

185
00:11:53,030 --> 00:11:55,860
Quit saying stupid crap!

186
00:11:58,950 --> 00:12:01,240
Ow!

187
00:12:01,620 --> 00:12:03,040
Wh-Who's she?!

188
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:07,750
Captain! This is no time to hypnotize
yourself and let people through!

189
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:10,290
The treasure on those boats is mine!

190
00:12:10,290 --> 00:12:11,750
You won't get a single berry!

191
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:15,260
Hold on to it for me
because I'm coming for it!

192
00:12:15,260 --> 00:12:16,420
That hurt!

193
00:12:16,420 --> 00:12:19,130
Who said you could
give them my treasure?!

194
00:12:19,130 --> 00:12:23,140
Well, you didn't have to whack me!

195
00:12:23,140 --> 00:12:25,520
What're you talking about?!
I just saved you!

196
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:26,640
Huh?

197
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:30,440
I forgot to mention, but don't look
at his ring when he starts counting!

198
00:12:30,850 --> 00:12:33,400
He's a hypnotist!

199
00:12:34,020 --> 00:12:35,650
H-Hypnotist?!

200
00:12:35,650 --> 00:12:37,530
So, where's Luffy?

201
00:12:37,530 --> 00:12:39,660
He got here first, right?

202
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:40,910
Dunno!

203
00:12:40,910 --> 00:12:43,620
He either chickened out or got lost!

204
00:12:44,580 --> 00:12:46,580
That'd mean he's lost.

205
00:12:46,580 --> 00:12:49,620
Man, just when we need him, too!

206
00:12:49,620 --> 00:12:51,500
Alright, I'll take command.

207
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:53,460
Go kick their butts! I'll cover you!

208
00:12:53,460 --> 00:12:55,960
What?! Hold on! Why me?!

209
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:58,340
There's no way I can
take on that huge army!

210
00:12:58,340 --> 00:12:59,720
I'm not exactly a fighter!

211
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:01,590
Don't be fooled just 'cause I'm a guy!

212
00:13:01,590 --> 00:13:05,180
I'm so scared that my legs
are shaking like crazy! See?!

213
00:13:05,180 --> 00:13:06,970
Big deal!

214
00:13:06,970 --> 00:13:09,940
I'm so scared my eyes are tearing up!

215
00:13:09,940 --> 00:13:12,020
Your eyes are bone dry!

216
00:13:12,020 --> 00:13:14,860
If you're gonna lie,
at least make it believable!

217
00:13:14,860 --> 00:13:16,980
That's rich coming from you!

218
00:13:16,980 --> 00:13:20,280
We don't have time
to deal with this...

219
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:23,820
Just trample over them
and head for the village, men!

220
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:29,620
H-Here they come!

221
00:13:29,620 --> 00:13:30,620
Oh, yeah!

222
00:13:30,620 --> 00:13:31,830
I have caltrops!

223
00:13:32,330 --> 00:13:34,040
So you do have some goodies!

224
00:13:34,040 --> 00:13:35,420
Gimme, gimme!

225
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:40,260
Take this!

226
00:13:40,260 --> 00:13:42,300
Caltrop Hell!

227
00:13:52,730 --> 00:13:55,150
Damn you, Nami!

228
00:13:55,150 --> 00:13:56,770
She's gonna pay for this!

229
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:07,530
I made it!

230
00:14:12,790 --> 00:14:16,500
Wh-Which way is the north shore?!

231
00:14:17,750 --> 00:14:20,760
Straight north!
Straight north! Straight north!

232
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:28,810
Which way is north?!

233
00:14:28,810 --> 00:14:30,430
Oww!

234
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:34,400
Alright! We got 'em!

235
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:35,400
Now, then...!

236
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:38,520
Lethal Lead Star!

237
00:14:41,150 --> 00:14:42,320
Bastard!

238
00:14:42,690 --> 00:14:43,820
Way to go!

239
00:14:43,820 --> 00:14:45,570
Keep it up, now!

240
00:14:45,570 --> 00:14:47,450
I'm gonna take a breather.

241
00:14:47,450 --> 00:14:49,910
But it hasn't even been five minutes!

242
00:14:49,910 --> 00:14:50,870
Wh-What is it?!

243
00:14:51,620 --> 00:14:53,580
There are caltrops behind us too...

244
00:14:53,580 --> 00:14:54,620
Are you stupid?!

245
00:14:54,620 --> 00:14:56,380
You dropped 'em there!

246
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,590
Outta the damn way!

247
00:15:08,430 --> 00:15:11,520
Do you seriously think
you can stop us?

248
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:15,730
Let's go, guys!

249
00:15:15,730 --> 00:15:17,600
Captain Kuro is waiting!

250
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:19,440
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

251
00:15:23,030 --> 00:15:24,280
Wh-What the...?!

252
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:27,240
Let go, you bastard! Dammit, let go!

253
00:15:27,570 --> 00:15:28,740
Damn you!

254
00:15:28,740 --> 00:15:30,490
Take this! You bastard!

255
00:15:30,490 --> 00:15:33,250
I... can't...

256
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:36,580
let you get past this slope.

257
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:42,210
This is just another
one of my lies...

258
00:15:43,050 --> 00:15:47,720
so it'll be just another
ordinary day for the village.

259
00:15:47,720 --> 00:15:50,970
I absolutely will not let you pass!

260
00:15:50,970 --> 00:15:52,180
Damn brat! Shut up!

261
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:56,940
You bitch!

262
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,940
Oww!

263
00:16:02,770 --> 00:16:03,860
Are you...?!

264
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:07,490
That's enough now!

265
00:16:09,820 --> 00:16:11,450
Hey, you guys!

266
00:16:11,450 --> 00:16:15,080
Quit bothering with them
and get going already!

267
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:17,920
Have you forgotten
this is Captain Kuro's plan?!

268
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:19,790
If anything derails it,

269
00:16:20,290 --> 00:16:22,750
he'll kill every last one of us!

270
00:16:22,750 --> 00:16:25,590
Do you understand that,
you dumbasses?!

271
00:16:25,590 --> 00:16:26,720
W-Well, uh...

272
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:28,720
Yeah, let's hurry to the village!

273
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:34,850
Stop...

274
00:16:34,850 --> 00:16:36,270
Dammit...

275
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:38,310
Stop!

276
00:16:38,940 --> 00:16:40,940
Stop... Don't go to the village!

277
00:16:40,940 --> 00:16:42,020
Shut up!

278
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:51,950
Stop!

279
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:53,700
Please...!

280
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:56,450
Please don't kill everyone!

281
00:16:56,450 --> 00:16:58,290
I love this village!

282
00:16:59,290 --> 00:17:01,420
I want to protect it!

283
00:17:16,770 --> 00:17:19,310
Wh-What is this, Captain Jango?!

284
00:17:19,310 --> 00:17:21,900
Nobody said the village
had guys like these!

285
00:17:22,940 --> 00:17:24,400
About time...

286
00:17:28,030 --> 00:17:30,530
Why the hell are these guys
such pushovers?!

287
00:17:30,530 --> 00:17:31,530
Beats me!

288
00:17:31,530 --> 00:17:33,240
I'm not satisfied either!

289
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:37,580
Nami! I can't believe you
kicked me down the slope!

290
00:17:37,580 --> 00:17:39,410
Usopp, you jerk!

291
00:17:39,410 --> 00:17:42,040
You didn't say which way was north!

292
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,670
Who are these guys?

293
00:17:52,340 --> 00:17:54,260
They're late...

294
00:17:54,260 --> 00:18:02,440
I thought they knew full well what
happens to those who derail my plans.

295
00:18:08,780 --> 00:18:11,400
Taking their sweet time like this...

296
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:14,910
Well, if they've forgotten even that…

297
00:18:16,910 --> 00:18:18,740
then I'll slaughter them all!

298
00:18:31,760 --> 00:18:34,430
Y-You guys are that strong?!

299
00:18:37,390 --> 00:18:40,390
What took you guys so long?!

300
00:18:41,390 --> 00:18:44,350
You're the one who
got me stuck back there!

301
00:18:44,350 --> 00:18:47,360
I didn't mean to, okay?!
I didn't have a choice!

302
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:51,360
Besides, one of us getting free was
better than both of us staying stuck.

303
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:53,110
Then you should've stayed!

304
00:18:53,780 --> 00:18:55,030
Seriously!

305
00:18:55,030 --> 00:18:59,530
How am I supposed to know
where north is or isn't?!

306
00:18:59,530 --> 00:19:00,660
What?!

307
00:19:00,660 --> 00:19:03,290
You're the one who
ran off all confident!

308
00:19:04,290 --> 00:19:07,170
Well, I was just trying to help you.

309
00:19:07,170 --> 00:19:09,380
Night is long gone now...

310
00:19:09,710 --> 00:19:13,300
and Captain Kuro
has a short temper...

311
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:16,220
Hey, men!

312
00:19:16,220 --> 00:19:20,470
Don't tell me you couldn't
handle two measly brats!

313
00:19:25,230 --> 00:19:26,520
Listen!

314
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:29,610
We don't have time
to be dilly-dallying here!

315
00:19:30,190 --> 00:19:33,570
If our enemy is strong,
we just need to be even stronger!

316
00:19:33,570 --> 00:19:36,570
Now watch this ring closely!

317
00:19:36,570 --> 00:19:39,450
On "one, two, Jango,"
you guys will grow strong.

318
00:19:39,450 --> 00:19:43,750
Your wounds will completely heal,
and you will grow stronger and stronger!

319
00:19:43,750 --> 00:19:46,460
What are they doing?

320
00:19:46,460 --> 00:19:48,210
It's hypnosis!

321
00:19:48,210 --> 00:19:50,590
He's trying to convince
them to be stronger!

322
00:19:50,590 --> 00:19:51,840
How ridiculous!

323
00:19:51,840 --> 00:19:53,170
One...

324
00:19:53,170 --> 00:19:54,590
two...

325
00:19:55,090 --> 00:19:56,840
Jango!

326
00:20:00,220 --> 00:20:01,140
No way!

327
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:17,150
H-He destroyed part of the cliff!

328
00:20:17,150 --> 00:20:19,240
Talk about power!

329
00:20:19,990 --> 00:20:22,700
That's some effective hypnosis!

330
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:26,200
With an army that strong...

331
00:20:28,540 --> 00:20:29,790
Go!

332
00:20:29,790 --> 00:20:32,210
Crush anyone who gets in the way!

333
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:45,560
Get back, you guys!

334
00:20:46,020 --> 00:20:48,270
We'll handle this!

335
00:20:51,940 --> 00:20:53,020
Hey, Luffy!

336
00:20:57,150 --> 00:20:58,240
Luffy?!

337
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:05,660
You got hypnotized too?!

338
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:15,800
He's so simple-minded...!

339
00:21:19,050 --> 00:21:21,550
Gum-Gum...

340
00:21:21,550 --> 00:21:26,060
Gatling!

341
00:21:35,650 --> 00:21:37,400
Damn you, Captain Kuro...

342
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:39,740
Thinking he'd have no impact
was a mistake!

343
00:21:40,280 --> 00:21:42,860
They're no ordinary brats!

344
00:22:02,550 --> 00:22:04,550
Where's he off to now?!

345
00:22:07,890 --> 00:22:09,220
What's he gonna do?!

346
00:22:19,110 --> 00:22:21,900
Go, Luffy!

347
00:22:23,740 --> 00:22:25,620
He's gonna destroy the ship!

348
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:35,710
No, he's not!

349
00:22:35,710 --> 00:22:39,590
He's gonna crush us with it!

350
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:43,260
Please do something, Captain!

351
00:22:46,760 --> 00:22:48,760
On "one, two, Jango,"
you'll get sleepy!

352
00:22:51,270 --> 00:22:52,020
One...

353
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,350
two...

354
00:22:54,100 --> 00:22:55,650
Jango!

355
00:23:29,550 --> 00:23:32,180
Looks like they're
just about wiped out!

356
00:23:32,180 --> 00:23:33,220
I'd say so.

357
00:23:33,220 --> 00:23:34,730
Hey!

358
00:23:34,730 --> 00:23:37,600
Never mind that,
Luffy's been crushed!

359
00:23:38,190 --> 00:23:39,690
He won't die.

360
00:23:39,690 --> 00:23:43,360
Just worry about your own wounds.

361
00:23:46,070 --> 00:23:48,450
Damn that brat!

362
00:23:48,450 --> 00:23:50,660
Now the plan is all but ruined!

363
00:23:50,660 --> 00:23:52,830
If Captain Kuro saw this,

364
00:23:53,330 --> 00:23:55,580
he'd slaughter all of us too!

365
00:23:56,830 --> 00:23:58,120
Hey, Buchi!

366
00:23:58,120 --> 00:24:00,380
Come look at this mess!

367
00:24:00,380 --> 00:24:02,880
What the hell?!

368
00:24:03,250 --> 00:24:05,090
We still have our trump card!

369
00:24:05,510 --> 00:24:08,890
Come forth, Meowban Brothers!

370
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:23,820
It is Klahadore from the mansion!

371
00:24:23,820 --> 00:24:27,400
Why is he heading
for the shore so early...?!

372
00:05:32,980 --> 00:05:35,900
"One-Two" Jango
Acting Captain of the Black Cat Pirates

373
00:05:32,980 --> 00:05:35,900
"One-Two" Jango
Acting Captain of the Black Cat Pirates

374
00:05:32,980 --> 00:05:35,900
"One-Two" Jango
Acting Captain of the Black Cat Pirates

